{"name": "wtforms-alchemy", "metadata": {"name": "WTForms-Alchemy", "version": "0.19.0", "classifiers": ["Environment :: Web Environment", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Topic :: Internet :: WWW/HTTP :: Dynamic Content", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules"], "home_page": "https://github.com/kvesteri/wtforms-alchemy", "license": "BSD", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["SQLAlchemy", "WTForms", "WTForms-Components", "SQLAlchemy-Utils"], "summary": "Generates WTForms forms from SQLAlchemy models.", "upload_time": 1731924366}, "documentation": ["\nWTForms-Alchemy\n---------------\n\nGenerates WTForms forms from SQLAlchemy models.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "wtforms_alchemy.validators", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "wtforms_alchemy.validators.Unique", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "wtforms_alchemy.validators.Unique.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "column", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "get_session", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "message", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.validators.Unique.query", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.validators.Unique._check_for_session", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "model", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.validators.Unique._syntaxes_as_tuples", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "form", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "field", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "column", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Converts a set of different syntaxes into a tuple of tuples"]}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.validators.Unique.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "form", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "field", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "wtforms_alchemy.validators.Unique.field_flags", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Checks field values unicity against specified table fields.\n\n```\nparam column\n\nInstrumentedAttribute object, eg. User.name, or\nColumn object, eg. user.c.name, or\na field name, eg. 'name' or\na tuple of InstrumentedAttributes, eg. (User.name, User.email) or\na dictionary mapping field names to InstrumentedAttributes, eg.\n{\n\nsource:10: (ERROR/3) Unexpected indentation.\n\n'name': User.name,\n'email': User.email\n\nsource:12: (WARNING/2) Block quote ends without a blank line; unexpected unindent.\n\nsource:12: (INFO/1) Unexpected possible title overline or transition.\nTreating it as ordinary text because it's so short.\n\n}\n\nparam get_session\n\nA function that returns a SQAlchemy Session. This parameter is not\nneeded if the given model supports Flask-SQLAlchemy styled query\nparameter.\n\nparam message\n\nThe error message.\n```\n"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "wtforms_alchemy.utils.choice_type_coerce_factory", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "type_", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return a function needed to coerce a ChoiceTyped column. This function is\nthen passed to generated SelectField as the default coerce function.\n\n```\nparam type\n\nChoiceType object\n```\n"]}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.utils.strip_string", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.utils.is_scalar", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.utils.null_or_unicode", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.utils.null_or_int", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.utils.flatten", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "list_", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.utils.is_number", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "type", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.utils.is_number_range", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "type", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.utils.is_date_column", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "column", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.utils.table", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "model", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.utils.find_entity", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "coll", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "model", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Find object in `coll` that matches `data`"]}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.utils.translated_attributes", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "model", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return translated attributes for current model class. See\n[SQLAlchemy-i18n package] for more information about translatable\nattributes.\n\n```\nparam model\n\nSQLAlchemy declarative model class\n```\n\n[sqlalchemy-i18n package]: https://github.com/kvesteri/sqlalchemy-i18n\n"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "wtforms_alchemy.utils.ClassMap", "bases": ["OrderedDict"], "methods": [{"name": "wtforms_alchemy.utils.ClassMap.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "items", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.utils.ClassMap.__contains__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "key", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Checks if given key exists in by first trying to find an exact match.\nIf no exact match is found then this method iterates trhough keys\nand tries to check if given key is either:\n\n> 1. A subclass of one of the keys\n> 2. An instance of one of the keys\n\nThe first check has the time complexity of O(1) whereas the second\ncheck has O(n).\n\nExample:\n\n```\nclass A(object):\n    pass\n\n\nclass B(object):\n    pass\n\n\nclass A2(A):\n    pass\n\n\nclass_map = ClassMap({A: 1, B: 2})\nassert B in class_map\nassert A in class_map\nassert A2 in class_map\nassert B() in class_map\nassert A() in class_map\nassert A2() in class_map\n```\n"]}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.utils.ClassMap.__getitem__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "key", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns the item matching a key. The key matching has the same\ncharasteristics as \\_\\_contains\\_\\_ method.\n\nExample:\n\n```\nclass A(object):\n    pass\n\n\nclass B(object):\n    pass\n\n\nclass A2(A):\n    pass\n\n\nclass_map = ClassMap({A: 1, B: 2})\nassert class_map[B] == 2\nassert class_map[A] == 1\nassert class_map[A2] == 1\nassert class_map[B()] == 2\nassert class_map[A()] == 1\nassert class_map[A2()] == 1\n```\n"]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["An ordered dictionary with keys as classes. ClassMap has the following\ncharasteristics:\n\n    1. Checking if a key exists not only matches exact classes but also\n    subclasses and objects which are instances of a ClassMap key.\n\n    2. Getting an item of ClassMap with a key matches subclasses and\n    instances also."]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "wtforms_alchemy.model_form_meta_factory", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "base", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Create a new class usable as a metaclass for the\n{func}`model_form_factory`. You only need to concern yourself with this if\nyou desire to have a custom metclass. Otherwise, a default class is\ncreated and is used as a metaclass on {func}`model_form_factory`.\n\n```\nparam base\n\nThe base class to use for the meta class. This is an optional\nparameter that defaults to . If you want to\nprovide your own, your class must derive from this class and\nnot directly from type.\n\nreturn\n\nA new class suitable as a metaclass for the actual model form.\nTherefore, it should be passed as the meta argument to\n.\n```\n\nExample usage:\n\n```python\nfrom wtforms.form import FormMeta\n\n\nclass MyModelFormMeta(FormMeta):\n    # do some metaclass magic here\n    pass\n\nModelFormMeta = model_form_meta_factory(MyModelFormMeta)\nModelForm = model_form_factory(meta=ModelFormMeta)\n```\n"]}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.model_form_factory", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "base", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "meta", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "**defaults", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Create a base class for all model forms to derive from.\n\n```\nparam base\n\nClass that should be used as a base for the returned class.\nBy default, this is WTForms's base class\n.\n\nparam meta\n\nA metaclass to use on this class. Normally, you do not need to\nprovide this value, but if you want, you should check out\n.\n\nreturn\n\nA class to be used as the base class for all forms that should be\nconnected to a SQLAlchemy model class.\n```\n\nAdditional arguments provided to the form override the default\nconfiguration as described in {ref}`custom_base`.\n"]}], "variables": [{"name": "wtforms_alchemy.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.ModelFormMeta", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.ModelForm", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "wtforms_alchemy.ModelCreateForm", "bases": ["ModelForm"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.ModelUpdateForm", "bases": ["ModelForm"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [{"name": "wtforms_alchemy.ModelUpdateForm.Meta", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "wtforms_alchemy.ModelUpdateForm.Meta.all_fields_optional", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.ModelUpdateForm.Meta.assign_required", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "documentation": []}, {"name": "wtforms_alchemy.ModelSearchForm", "bases": ["ModelForm"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [{"name": "wtforms_alchemy.ModelSearchForm.Meta", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "wtforms_alchemy.ModelSearchForm.Me